import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['away_score'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='away_score', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['away_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['away_score'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['away_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of away scores?')
    plt.xlabel('Away Score')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['goal_difference'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='goal_difference', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['goal_difference'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['goal_difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['goal_difference'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of goal difference?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Goal Difference')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['result'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar', color=['green', 'red', 'gray'])
    plt.title('What is the most common result (win, loss, or draw)?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Result')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(['Win', 'Loss', 'Draw'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['result'] = data['result'].astype('category')
    sns.scatterplot(x='home_score', y='away_score', hue='result', data=data)
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Home Score Mean')
    plt.axhline(data['away_score'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='Away Score Mean')
    plt.title("How does the home team's score compare to the away team's score?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
